This link contains different port data, but I chose air cargo only. Mainly because
during the 21-22 period. The GDP of HK increased while the total port change decreased,
this is because during that time, the value of electronic goods increased while the
volume of things decreased. This decreases the overall port volume as the River Freight
Movement decreased a lot, which brought down the average.

A good way to capture the GDP change is to capture the value of goods, and that is what 
air cargo can do, as air cargo is responsible for luxury goods, it is the most efficient
tracker for GDP compared to the entire port volume change itself.